Jack Enjo, the Ultimate Pyrotechnician's room. Honestly, the room itself isn't that big - if you've ever been on a cruise ship in the lowest class, it's about as big as the rooms there. But what is here is decently nice. The bed is nice and large, and feels rather nice to sleep in. There's a TV opposite of the bed, too, but there's not so much as a remote in the room - it seems like it won't turn on. Looking to the left while being on the bed reveals a window that shows off the outside in all of its glory. It doesn't seem like you can open the window, but there are curtains to block off the windows at the very least. Other than that, there's a small closet with duplicates of your OC's clothes as well as a notebook and a pencil for good measure. There's also trash can in the corner, useful for getting rid of evidence. Finally, the room also has a bathroom, which seems to be pretty typical. It's nice, and has everything you need, but... there's not much more to say.
